text: Stull is an unincorporated community in Douglas County, Kansas, United States. It was created in 1857. It is about 7 miles west of Lawrence, and it's about 10 miles east of Topeka. ==The Stull Cemetery== The Stull Cemetery has rumors that it is haunted. These rumors involve Satan, the occult, and that the cemetery is a way to get into Hell. ==References== ==Other websites== * Douglas County Maps: Current , Historic , KDOT Category:Unincorporated communities in Douglas County, Kansas
title: Stull, Kansas
